1
00:00:36,500 --> 00:00:37,767
<i>The investigation
is still focused</i>

2
00:00:37,900 --> 00:00:40,100
<i>on finding the driver
that hit Jessica.</i>

3
00:00:40,233 --> 00:00:42,433
<i>I hope whoever hit our sister
feels guilty.</i>

4
00:00:42,567 --> 00:00:44,600
<i> But Hazel won't stop, Jeff.</i>

5
00:00:44,733 --> 00:00:47,133
<i>She'll keep insisting that
I'm the one who killed Jessica.</i>

6
00:00:47,267 --> 00:00:48,933
<i> The burden of proof is on her.</i>

7
00:00:49,067 --> 00:00:50,967
<i>They said Coleen's
been sent home.</i>

8
00:00:51,100 --> 00:00:52,367
<i>- Why?
- She claimed</i>

9
00:00:52,500 --> 00:00:54,033
<i> that she didn't push Jessica.</i>

10
00:00:54,167 --> 00:00:55,533
<i> What a liar.</i>

11
00:00:55,667 --> 00:00:57,833
<i>Well, Mrs. Cruz,
there's no other witness</i>

12
00:00:57,967 --> 00:00:59,467
<i> to contradict her statement.</i>

13
00:00:59,600 --> 00:01:03,133
<i>Then find evidence against
that woman, Attorney.</i>

14
00:01:03,267 --> 00:01:05,233
<i>Or are you just too lazy
to look for it?</i>

15
00:01:05,367 --> 00:01:07,033
<i>If you won't do it, fine,
I'll handle it myself.</i>

16
00:01:07,200 --> 00:01:09,333
<i>Are you really going
to expose Coleen?</i>

17
00:01:09,467 --> 00:01:11,400
<i> What I need now is perception.</i>

18
00:01:11,533 --> 00:01:14,333
<i>I have to win
the people's sympathy.</i>

19
00:01:14,467 --> 00:01:16,700
<i>So they'll believe
that it wasn't</i>

20
00:01:16,833 --> 00:01:19,533
<i>just the hit-and-run driver
who killed Jessica,</i>

21
00:01:19,667 --> 00:01:21,200
<i>but also the one who pushed her.</i>

22
00:01:21,333 --> 00:01:23,667
<i>And here's my guest
for tonight's live interview...</i>

23
00:01:24,233 --> 00:01:27,100
<i>Mrs. Hazel Cruz,
the hit-and-run victim</i>

24
00:01:27,233 --> 00:01:29,133
<i> that broke everyone's heart.</i>

25
00:01:29,267 --> 00:01:33,233
<i>I'm calling out to the driver
who hit my daughter.</i>

26
00:01:33,833 --> 00:01:35,667
<i> And not just the driver,</i>

27
00:01:35,800 --> 00:01:38,600
<i>but also the person who pushed
Jessica.</i>

28
00:01:38,733 --> 00:01:41,033
<i>No matter what happens,
she won't confess.</i>

29
00:01:41,200 --> 00:01:44,533
<i>Even her mother and siblings...</i>

30
00:01:44,667 --> 00:01:46,700
<i> they are all protecting her.</i>

31
00:01:46,833 --> 00:01:48,900
<i>So the person who pushed
your daughter was a woman?</i>

32
00:01:49,033 --> 00:01:49,933
<i> Yes.</i>

33
00:01:50,067 --> 00:01:51,233
<i>Coleen's getting bashed online.</i>

34
00:01:51,367 --> 00:01:52,767
<i>That's the problem
with social media.</i>

35
00:01:52,900 --> 00:01:54,333
<i> People are so quick to judge.</i>

36
00:01:54,467 --> 00:01:56,267
<i> So many hate comments.</i>

37
00:01:56,400 --> 00:01:58,700
<i>They all believe
I pushed Jessica.</i>

38
00:01:58,833 --> 00:02:00,533
<i>Didn't you really see
what happened</i>

39
00:02:00,667 --> 00:02:02,100
<i> before Jessica got hit?</i>

40
00:02:02,233 --> 00:02:04,100
<i> None of us saw it, Bro.</i>

41
00:02:04,633 --> 00:02:06,900
<i>Wait, are you doubting
Coleen now?</i>

42
00:02:07,533 --> 00:02:10,000
<i>I don't know,
I'm just so confused.</i>

43
00:02:10,133 --> 00:02:12,333
<i> Coleen pushed Jessica.</i>

44
00:02:12,800 --> 00:02:15,400
<i>Once I prove it,
they'd better be ready.</i>

45
00:02:15,567 --> 00:02:17,633
<i> Especially Felma.</i>

46
00:02:17,767 --> 00:02:18,667
<i> Because she gave birth</i>

47
00:02:18,800 --> 00:02:20,400
<i>to the one who killed
my daughter.</i>

48
00:02:23,233 --> 00:02:24,333
<i> Yes, Manuel?</i>

49
00:02:34,867 --> 00:02:37,767
Mommy's here, sweetheart.

50
00:02:40,300 --> 00:02:41,633
Jessica.

51
00:02:58,400 --> 00:03:00,000
What do you want to talk about?

52
00:03:00,933 --> 00:03:03,133
About how you're destroying
Coleen on social media.

53
00:03:04,600 --> 00:03:06,300
I'm not destroying her.

54
00:03:07,800 --> 00:03:09,567
I'm just looking for people
who can help me

55
00:03:09,700 --> 00:03:12,467
to get justice
for what happened to Jessica.

56
00:03:14,167 --> 00:03:16,100
You just want to hurt Felma!

57
00:03:16,400 --> 00:03:17,567
You're using Coleen
to get back at her!

58
00:03:19,700 --> 00:03:20,500
Why?

59
00:03:22,333 --> 00:03:23,800
Are you scared?

60
00:03:25,300 --> 00:03:27,100
Scared that your mistress
might get hurt?

61
00:03:29,133 --> 00:03:33,667
Manuel, that woman
raised a monster.

62
00:03:34,400 --> 00:03:36,733
A monster who killed
our daughter!

63
00:03:37,300 --> 00:03:38,933
Coleen isn't a monster!

64
00:03:39,067 --> 00:03:40,867
And she didn't kill Jessica!

65
00:03:52,367 --> 00:03:56,267
If you truly believe that Coleen

66
00:03:56,433 --> 00:03:59,567
didn't push Jessica
and have no doubt whatsoever...

67
00:04:00,467 --> 00:04:04,733
then say it, swear in front
of our daughter's grave.

68
00:04:09,867 --> 00:04:10,767
Didang.

69
00:04:11,000 --> 00:04:12,633
- Ma'am.
- Where are Manuel and Jeffrey?

70
00:04:12,767 --> 00:04:14,667
They left earlier.

71
00:04:14,967 --> 00:04:15,667
What?

72
00:04:15,900 --> 00:04:16,967
Where did they go?

73
00:04:17,100 --> 00:04:18,933
Ma'am, they didn't say.

74
00:04:19,067 --> 00:04:21,700
Maybe to therapy?
He had a session today, right?

75
00:04:21,833 --> 00:04:24,133
I was supposed to go
with Manuel.

76
00:04:24,267 --> 00:04:25,300
We were going to talk

77
00:04:25,433 --> 00:04:28,967
to Dr. Richard
about the psychologist.

78
00:04:33,067 --> 00:04:34,867
- Move over, will you?
- Why won't you answer, Manuel?

79
00:04:35,967 --> 00:04:39,200
Because deep down in your heart,
you have doubts too.

80
00:04:40,533 --> 00:04:41,567
Admit it, Manuel!

81
00:04:42,267 --> 00:04:43,367
Admit it!

82
00:04:44,700 --> 00:04:45,900
I don't owe you an explanation

83
00:04:46,033 --> 00:04:47,667
about what I believe.

84
00:04:48,567 --> 00:04:49,833
But I owe that to my daughter.

85
00:04:50,967 --> 00:04:52,033
Move aside!

86
00:04:58,467 --> 00:04:59,467
Dear...

87
00:05:00,100 --> 00:05:02,000
I truly believe that...

88
00:05:03,333 --> 00:05:05,233
Coleen didn't kill you.

89
00:05:06,633 --> 00:05:07,700
And that's the truth, dear.

90
00:05:09,100 --> 00:05:11,100
You bastard, Manuel!
What are you even saying?

91
00:05:11,900 --> 00:05:13,000
Hazel, stop this already!

92
00:05:13,967 --> 00:05:15,500
Or I swear!
Don't make me lose control!

93
00:05:17,100 --> 00:05:18,600
Manuel's not answering
his phone.

94
00:05:31,500 --> 00:05:32,667
Hello, Mom?

95
00:05:32,800 --> 00:05:34,233
Hello, Jeff? Son.

96
00:05:34,833 --> 00:05:35,967
Are you at the hospital?

97
00:05:36,767 --> 00:05:37,600
What?

98
00:05:37,867 --> 00:05:39,167
Stop disrespecting our daughter!

99
00:05:39,300 --> 00:05:40,600
Even her memory!

100
00:05:41,400 --> 00:05:42,333
That's Hazel!

101
00:05:43,467 --> 00:05:45,567
Where are you and your dad?

102
00:05:45,700 --> 00:05:46,867
<i> All this time,</i>

103
00:05:47,000 --> 00:05:48,100
<i>you're the one who's been
disrespecting our daughter.</i>

104
00:05:48,767 --> 00:05:49,900
When she was still alive,

105
00:05:50,033 --> 00:05:52,233
you used her just to turn
my family against me!

106
00:05:53,100 --> 00:05:57,000
And now she's gone,
you're still using Jessica!

107
00:05:57,267 --> 00:05:58,967
We're not annulled yet.

108
00:06:00,900 --> 00:06:06,300
That means I'm still
your legal wife.

109
00:06:06,667 --> 00:06:09,967
Jessica and I are still
your legal family.

110
00:06:10,333 --> 00:06:12,433
We're at the cemetery.

111
00:06:12,567 --> 00:06:15,433
Dad asked me to come with him
so he could talk to Hazel.

112
00:06:15,567 --> 00:06:16,600
<i> What?</i>

113
00:06:17,067 --> 00:06:18,233
Why?

114
00:06:18,867 --> 00:06:23,700
Dad wants to talk to Hazel about
that viral video of Coleen.

115
00:06:24,267 --> 00:06:26,867
Oh, that conversation
won't lead anywhere.

116
00:06:27,333 --> 00:06:28,933
Take your father home.

117
00:06:30,767 --> 00:06:31,767
Yes, Mom.

118
00:06:32,400 --> 00:06:34,400
When did your love
for Jessica disappear?

119
00:06:36,833 --> 00:06:39,600
The moment you saw your kids
with Felma again?

120
00:06:40,700 --> 00:06:43,167
My love for Jessica
never disappeared.

121
00:06:43,300 --> 00:06:44,367
Don't you dare question that.

122
00:06:45,467 --> 00:06:46,500
Love?

123
00:06:47,700 --> 00:06:51,633
You're doing nothing
to get justice for Jessica.

124
00:06:52,733 --> 00:06:55,967
If you really loved her,
you wouldn't stand for this.

125
00:06:56,833 --> 00:06:59,067
The person who did this
should be punished.

126
00:07:00,067 --> 00:07:01,600
The one who killed Jessica
will be punished.

127
00:07:01,733 --> 00:07:02,933
The police are already
looking for him.

128
00:07:03,667 --> 00:07:04,667
She's right there at your house.

129
00:07:05,600 --> 00:07:06,933
You just have to turn her in.

130
00:07:08,033 --> 00:07:10,000
Stop dragging Coleen
through the mud.

131
00:07:10,133 --> 00:07:12,167
Or else I'll sue.

132
00:07:12,300 --> 00:07:13,200
Sue me for what?

133
00:07:14,300 --> 00:07:15,267
Slander?

134
00:07:16,033 --> 00:07:18,300
I didn't even mention any names
on the FriendsBook Live

135
00:07:18,433 --> 00:07:19,567
of Detective XY's.

136
00:07:20,133 --> 00:07:21,133
You think that's the only thing

137
00:07:21,267 --> 00:07:22,533
I can sue you for?

138
00:07:23,700 --> 00:07:26,200
Maybe you forgot you forged
my signature

139
00:07:26,333 --> 00:07:27,400
to get me discharged
from the hospital.

140
00:07:28,333 --> 00:07:29,500
You're a monster, Manuel.

141
00:07:30,167 --> 00:07:31,333
Get out of here.

142
00:07:31,467 --> 00:07:33,533
And don't you ever come back to
my daughter's grave, understood?

143
00:07:33,667 --> 00:07:36,033
I have every right to visit
my child whenever I want.

144
00:07:36,900 --> 00:07:38,400
I let you have the last wake

145
00:07:38,533 --> 00:07:40,433
and the burial because I didn't
want you to lose control.

146
00:07:40,567 --> 00:07:41,967
I didn't want
our daughter disrespected.

147
00:07:42,100 --> 00:07:44,000
But not anymore!
You won't stop me now!

148
00:07:44,433 --> 00:07:46,567
Leave! Just get lost! Leave!

149
00:07:46,700 --> 00:07:47,767
Jessica doesn't need you.

150
00:07:47,933 --> 00:07:49,500
- Hazel! Enough!
- Get out of here!

151
00:07:49,633 --> 00:07:51,100
- I said, get out of here!
- Stop! Stop!

152
00:07:51,233 --> 00:07:53,367
We're leaving!
We're leaving! Enough!

153
00:07:53,500 --> 00:07:54,500
- Let's go.
- Remember this,

154
00:07:54,633 --> 00:07:56,200
I will do everything to put
Coleen behind bars.

155
00:07:56,333 --> 00:07:57,700
Mark my words, Manuel!

156
00:07:58,900 --> 00:08:00,133
I will do whatever it takes!

157
00:08:07,100 --> 00:08:09,633
Ma'am, can you please calm down?

158
00:08:09,767 --> 00:08:10,833
You're too worked up.

159
00:08:12,267 --> 00:08:14,267
I'm just worried, Didang.

160
00:08:15,100 --> 00:08:17,767
We don't know
what Hazel might do.

161
00:08:18,167 --> 00:08:19,800
What if she hurts Manuel again?

162
00:08:19,933 --> 00:08:20,967
Pushes him?

163
00:08:21,100 --> 00:08:24,433
Or targets the part of his body

164
00:08:24,600 --> 00:08:26,533
she knows is weak?

165
00:08:27,833 --> 00:08:29,800
Ma'am, I get it.

166
00:08:30,133 --> 00:08:31,433
But please calm down, okay?

167
00:08:32,000 --> 00:08:34,833
Didn't you already tell them
to go home? He and Jeffrey?

168
00:08:36,367 --> 00:08:38,700
Wait, sit down first,
just relax.

169
00:08:38,833 --> 00:08:40,233
I'll make you some tea.

170
00:08:41,033 --> 00:08:42,767
It's just so frustrating.

171
00:08:42,900 --> 00:08:45,000
Why did they even go there
in the first place?

172
00:08:45,133 --> 00:08:47,167
You're not jealous
or anything, are you?

173
00:08:47,300 --> 00:08:48,967
No! I mean...

174
00:08:49,100 --> 00:08:49,700
Of course,

175
00:08:49,833 --> 00:08:51,967
you can worry, right?

176
00:08:52,100 --> 00:08:53,467
Yes, you're worried.

177
00:08:53,600 --> 00:08:54,700
I can feel it.

178
00:08:54,867 --> 00:08:57,033
Oh, I can definitely
feel it, Ma'am.

179
00:08:57,167 --> 00:08:58,200
Didang.

180
00:09:02,733 --> 00:09:04,000
Dear, did you see that?

181
00:09:06,233 --> 00:09:10,300
Even until your death,
your father still chose

182
00:09:10,433 --> 00:09:11,833
his illegitimate
family over us.

183
00:09:13,667 --> 00:09:14,967
But don't worry.

184
00:09:16,400 --> 00:09:18,200
I meant what I told you.

185
00:09:19,933 --> 00:09:25,367
If I have to plant evidence,
I will.

186
00:09:28,100 --> 00:09:30,367
So that you can get the justice
you deserve.

187
00:09:32,167 --> 00:09:34,000
So we can get even with Coleen.

188
00:09:34,967 --> 00:09:36,967
Coleen and her entire family.

189
00:09:53,200 --> 00:09:54,467
Manuel...

190
00:09:54,600 --> 00:09:57,667
why did you meet with Hazel
without telling me?

191
00:09:58,833 --> 00:10:01,767
I just didn't want to add
to your worries.

192
00:10:01,933 --> 00:10:03,733
What if she did something
to you?

193
00:10:05,133 --> 00:10:07,000
Come on, I was with
Jeffrey, wasn't I?

194
00:10:08,767 --> 00:10:10,800
What if she brought people
with her?

195
00:10:10,933 --> 00:10:14,333
What if they beat Jeffrey up
and took you again?

196
00:10:18,300 --> 00:10:19,767
Why are you smiling?

197
00:10:24,267 --> 00:10:26,433
You're just scared to be away
from me.

198
00:10:28,000 --> 00:10:30,933
Manuel, I'm serious.

199
00:10:31,533 --> 00:10:33,167
Okay, okay, I'm sorry.

200
00:10:33,700 --> 00:10:35,933
I just can't forgive Hazel

201
00:10:36,100 --> 00:10:38,633
for what she did online.

202
00:10:38,767 --> 00:10:40,267
She's poisoning people's minds,

203
00:10:40,400 --> 00:10:41,800
making them believe
Coleen's a killer.

204
00:10:42,833 --> 00:10:47,500
And you think meeting her
will fix that?

205
00:10:47,633 --> 00:10:50,167
Look, you met with her,

206
00:10:50,300 --> 00:10:51,600
and what happened?

207
00:10:51,733 --> 00:10:54,100
All right, all right, I'm sorry.

208
00:10:54,233 --> 00:10:55,600
Don't be mad anymore.

209
00:10:57,367 --> 00:10:58,867
See? I'm fine.

210
00:10:59,500 --> 00:11:01,833
Jeffrey and I got home safely.

211
00:11:05,100 --> 00:11:06,367
I'm sorry, too.

212
00:11:08,033 --> 00:11:09,267
Didang was right.

213
00:11:10,000 --> 00:11:12,067
I overreacted.

214
00:11:12,200 --> 00:11:13,133
I was just scared

215
00:11:13,267 --> 00:11:15,367
of what Hazel might do to you.

216
00:11:23,067 --> 00:11:24,567
Don't worry anymore, Felma.

217
00:11:25,600 --> 00:11:27,967
Hazel won't come
between us again.

218
00:11:30,567 --> 00:11:33,867
And I won't ever leave you,
not anymore.

219
00:11:43,967 --> 00:11:46,633
I really thought mom and dad
were gonna fight for real.

220
00:11:47,367 --> 00:11:48,500
Good thing they made up.

221
00:11:50,800 --> 00:11:53,433
What about dad's meeting
with Hazel?

222
00:11:53,567 --> 00:11:55,200
How did that go?

223
00:11:55,333 --> 00:11:58,633
How many horns did Hazel
grow this time?

224
00:11:58,767 --> 00:12:00,633
Just one.

225
00:12:02,333 --> 00:12:05,867
She cried more than
she turned into a monster.

226
00:12:07,300 --> 00:12:09,300
I don't know, I kind of felt
what she was feeling.

227
00:12:10,500 --> 00:12:11,533
What?

228
00:12:12,267 --> 00:12:13,933
Wait, Jeffrey, are you taking
the devil's side now?

229
00:12:14,100 --> 00:12:14,800
No.

230
00:12:15,933 --> 00:12:17,900
But I think mom was right.

231
00:12:19,167 --> 00:12:21,067
It's just a mother's pain.

232
00:12:22,800 --> 00:12:24,733
She's looking
for someone to blame

233
00:12:24,867 --> 00:12:26,200
for losing Jessica.

234
00:12:27,500 --> 00:12:29,033
I kind of get that.

235
00:12:31,267 --> 00:12:32,833
It reminded me of Tetay.

236
00:12:35,400 --> 00:12:36,533
When Daisy took her away
from me,

237
00:12:36,667 --> 00:12:37,933
that's how I remembered.

238
00:12:39,867 --> 00:12:42,067
I remember I took it
all out on dad.

239
00:12:43,933 --> 00:12:45,600
It's hard to lose
a child, Andrea.

240
00:12:46,967 --> 00:12:48,400
Especially for someone
like Hazel.

241
00:12:50,033 --> 00:12:52,000
She'll never see
her daughter again.

242
00:12:53,067 --> 00:12:55,900
Yes, maybe I pity her,
but I pity dad even more.

243
00:12:56,733 --> 00:12:58,100
He didn't just lose a daughter.

244
00:12:58,667 --> 00:13:00,533
Another one might end up
in jail.

245
00:13:01,367 --> 00:13:02,800
Hazel made a threat.

246
00:13:03,667 --> 00:13:05,833
She said she'll do anything
to make Coleen pay.

247
00:13:16,767 --> 00:13:17,667
Coleen?

248
00:13:23,567 --> 00:13:24,600
Let's not wake her up.

249
00:13:24,733 --> 00:13:25,567
She's still sleeping.

250
00:13:32,033 --> 00:13:34,600
Jessica, Jessica.

251
00:13:35,667 --> 00:13:37,067
- Jessica...
- Coleen?

252
00:13:37,200 --> 00:13:38,867
- Jessica.
- Coleen, Coleen.

253
00:13:39,000 --> 00:13:40,900
- Jessica. Jessica.
- Coleen. Coleen.

254
00:13:42,167 --> 00:13:44,400
- Coleen! Coleen!
- Jessica!

255
00:13:44,533 --> 00:13:45,700
Coleen!

256
00:13:45,833 --> 00:13:47,900
Coleen, it's just a dream!
A dream, okay?

257
00:13:48,033 --> 00:13:50,633
Wake up! It's nothing
but a dream! It's nothing.

258
00:13:54,800 --> 00:13:55,833
Coleen.

259
00:13:59,600 --> 00:14:01,833
It's Jessica.

260
00:14:07,233 --> 00:14:10,067
I should've
held on to her tighter.

261
00:14:11,233 --> 00:14:15,533
I wish I could take back
everything I said to her.

262
00:14:16,467 --> 00:14:18,100
I wish she were still here.

263
00:14:20,300 --> 00:14:23,567
I wish she were still with us.

264
00:14:33,700 --> 00:14:35,667
If I had just held her tighter,

265
00:14:35,800 --> 00:14:37,800
maybe it wouldn't have happened.

266
00:14:39,567 --> 00:14:41,633
Maybe Hazel's right.

267
00:14:41,767 --> 00:14:42,800
Maybe I pushed her.

268
00:14:43,800 --> 00:14:45,200
I pushed Jessica.

269
00:14:45,333 --> 00:14:47,567
- Dear, no...
- Maybe Hazel's right.

270
00:14:47,700 --> 00:14:49,600
Coleen! Dear!

271
00:14:49,733 --> 00:14:52,200
No! No, okay?

272
00:14:52,333 --> 00:14:54,667
You didn't push Jessica.

273
00:14:54,800 --> 00:14:57,933
Coleen, you didn't push Jessica.

274
00:14:58,067 --> 00:15:02,067
Don't let Hazel's words
get into your head.

275
00:15:04,900 --> 00:15:06,967
What if she gets a witness?

276
00:15:07,633 --> 00:15:08,967
I'll go to prison.

277
00:15:09,100 --> 00:15:10,567
- No, dear.
- I'll go to prison.

278
00:15:10,700 --> 00:15:12,367
If she finds someone to testify,

279
00:15:12,500 --> 00:15:13,867
- that's not how it works, dear.
- I'll go to jail!

280
00:15:14,000 --> 00:15:16,100
Coleen, no, you won't go
to jail.

281
00:15:16,233 --> 00:15:17,867
Sweetheart.

282
00:15:18,000 --> 00:15:20,967
- Sweetheart, dear.
- Mom...

283
00:15:21,100 --> 00:15:24,833
I don't know what to do, Mom.

284
00:15:24,967 --> 00:15:26,533
Mom...

285
00:15:42,267 --> 00:15:43,500
<i> Okay, Coleen.</i>

286
00:15:44,500 --> 00:15:48,533
Your mother said you've barely
been sleeping

287
00:15:48,667 --> 00:15:50,433
these past few days?

288
00:15:50,567 --> 00:15:53,133
You've been zoning out a lot...

289
00:15:54,133 --> 00:15:59,333
crying and having bad dreams?

290
00:16:01,567 --> 00:16:04,567
Can you tell me what's going
through your mind...

291
00:16:05,933 --> 00:16:09,033
since after the accident?

292
00:16:10,700 --> 00:16:11,833
Guilt.

293
00:16:13,700 --> 00:16:16,700
That's what I feel
every single day.

294
00:16:20,000 --> 00:16:21,433
Can you tell me more?

295
00:16:22,533 --> 00:16:27,167
What happened keeps replaying.

296
00:16:28,200 --> 00:16:30,200
It's like a loop.

297
00:16:31,600 --> 00:16:36,900
I try to stop it, but it just
keeps coming back.

298
00:16:37,033 --> 00:16:40,267
I even hear her scream...

299
00:16:40,400 --> 00:16:43,700
even in my dreams.

300
00:16:46,233 --> 00:16:51,767
Coleen, guilt is a natural
part of grief.

301
00:16:52,800 --> 00:16:56,600
From what you're telling me,
I think...

302
00:16:56,733 --> 00:17:01,100
what you're describing
sounds like survivor's guilt.

303
00:17:02,100 --> 00:17:05,467
It's, it's a trauma
where you blame yourself

304
00:17:05,600 --> 00:17:08,600
for something that happened
beyond your control.

305
00:17:09,900 --> 00:17:12,900
Beyond my control?

306
00:17:13,033 --> 00:17:14,233
Doc...

307
00:17:15,200 --> 00:17:18,067
I was holding Jessica.

308
00:17:18,200 --> 00:17:20,067
If I'd held on tighter,

309
00:17:21,100 --> 00:17:23,633
I wouldn't have let go.

310
00:17:23,767 --> 00:17:26,400
She wouldn't have been hit.

311
00:17:27,167 --> 00:17:30,600
<i>But what if I only think
I pulled her?</i>

312
00:17:30,733 --> 00:17:34,533
Doc, what if I did kill
my sister?

313
00:17:36,200 --> 00:17:37,767
When did those thoughts start?

314
00:17:39,267 --> 00:17:40,733
You can't remember exactly?

315
00:17:41,733 --> 00:17:44,500
Your mom said it started
after you read

316
00:17:44,633 --> 00:17:47,400
all those hate comments online.

317
00:17:49,033 --> 00:17:53,233
But before that, you were sure
you didn't push Jessica.

318
00:17:53,367 --> 00:17:54,433
You've been consistent
about that.

319
00:17:54,567 --> 00:17:56,133
That's what everyone
who knows you believes.

320
00:17:56,267 --> 00:17:58,867
And that's what I believe, too.

321
00:18:02,500 --> 00:18:03,800
Coleen...

322
00:18:06,167 --> 00:18:07,900
you did not...

323
00:18:08,033 --> 00:18:09,967
kill your sister.

324
00:18:10,100 --> 00:18:12,067
You argued, yes,
you pulled her,

325
00:18:12,200 --> 00:18:14,500
and she pulled herself away
from you.

326
00:18:14,633 --> 00:18:16,833
That part, you couldn't control.

327
00:18:18,500 --> 00:18:22,767
Jessica's actions,
her decisions,

328
00:18:22,933 --> 00:18:25,233
were her own, not yours.

329
00:18:26,400 --> 00:18:30,033
What you're feeling right now,
that's grief.

330
00:18:30,567 --> 00:18:31,733
You feel this way because
you love her.

331
00:18:31,867 --> 00:18:33,133
You love Jessica.

332
00:18:33,267 --> 00:18:36,100
Yes, Doc, I love Jessica!

333
00:18:36,233 --> 00:18:38,800
I love her, she's my sister!

334
00:18:38,933 --> 00:18:41,667
I'm her big sister, but...

335
00:18:41,800 --> 00:18:44,467
I was supposed to protect her,

336
00:18:44,600 --> 00:18:48,600
not fight with her
but what did I do, Doc?

337
00:18:48,733 --> 00:18:51,267
<i> I didn't protect her.</i>

338
00:18:52,633 --> 00:18:54,900
I let her down, Doc.

339
00:18:55,067 --> 00:18:57,200
I let Jessica down.

340
00:18:58,433 --> 00:19:01,367
And because of that, she's gone.

341
00:19:01,500 --> 00:19:03,433
My sister's gone!

342
00:19:07,367 --> 00:19:09,900
<i> My sister!</i>

343
00:19:34,300 --> 00:19:35,533
Felma...

344
00:19:35,667 --> 00:19:37,267
what did the doctor say?

345
00:19:44,167 --> 00:19:47,667
Based on Dr. Darla's
initial findings...

346
00:19:48,900 --> 00:19:51,400
Coleen's guilt runs very deep.

347
00:19:52,667 --> 00:19:54,300
She blames herself...

348
00:19:55,333 --> 00:19:58,333
for what happened to Jessica,
even though she wasn't at fault.

349
00:20:02,600 --> 00:20:06,000
<i>Coleen is going through
what we call complicated grief.</i>

350
00:20:06,133 --> 00:20:07,800
<i> She's not just grieving.</i>

351
00:20:07,933 --> 00:20:10,000
<i> She's blaming herself, too.</i>

352
00:20:10,133 --> 00:20:12,900
<i>When grief gets this heavy,
it becomes punishment.</i>

353
00:20:13,933 --> 00:20:15,767
<i> Punishing herself?</i>

354
00:20:17,067 --> 00:20:18,800
<i>She keeps replaying
what happens,</i>

355
00:20:18,933 --> 00:20:21,567
<i>thinking about what she could've
done differently.</i>

356
00:20:21,700 --> 00:20:23,700
<i> All the what ifs.</i>

357
00:20:23,833 --> 00:20:25,500
<i>But the truth is that
she had no control over</i>

358
00:20:25,633 --> 00:20:26,700
<i> what happened that day.</i>

359
00:20:30,733 --> 00:20:33,533
So what can we do, Mom?

360
00:20:34,700 --> 00:20:38,600
We need to keep
reminding her that...

361
00:20:38,767 --> 00:20:41,167
none of this was her fault.

362
00:20:41,600 --> 00:20:44,800
Make her feel that
she's not alone.

363
00:20:45,600 --> 00:20:47,333
That she's surrounded by love.

364
00:20:48,700 --> 00:20:49,900
<i> Watch over her,</i>

365
00:20:50,033 --> 00:20:52,033
<i> but don't overdo it.</i>

366
00:20:52,167 --> 00:20:55,233
<i>Let her feel safe, not trapped.</i>

367
00:20:55,367 --> 00:20:59,167
<i>Okay? Encourage her to open up,</i>

368
00:20:59,300 --> 00:21:01,633
<i> but don't force her to talk.</i>

369
00:21:01,767 --> 00:21:03,300
<i> Even just sitting beside her</i>

370
00:21:03,433 --> 00:21:08,233
<i> in silence already helps.</i>

371
00:21:08,400 --> 00:21:10,033
<i>- Thank you, Doctor.
- Sure.</i>

372
00:21:10,167 --> 00:21:11,500
<i> We'll have another session.</i>

373
00:21:12,600 --> 00:21:14,633
<i>But if you notice
anything unusual</i>

374
00:21:14,767 --> 00:21:16,733
<i>or out of the ordinary
in her behavior,</i>

375
00:21:17,500 --> 00:21:19,200
<i> call me immediately, alright?</i>

376
00:21:19,333 --> 00:21:21,800
<i>Or bring her straight
to the hospital.</i>

377
00:21:23,233 --> 00:21:26,333
We all need to work together
for Coleen's recovery.

378
00:21:29,567 --> 00:21:31,200
I'll make a schedule.

379
00:21:32,267 --> 00:21:34,867
Let's take turns
watching over Coleen.

380
00:21:36,367 --> 00:21:37,400
I'll stay with her for now.

381
00:21:38,733 --> 00:21:40,167
I won't go to work for now, Mom.

382
00:21:48,267 --> 00:21:49,300
Andrea?

383
00:21:50,067 --> 00:21:51,400
- Dear.
- Mom?

384
00:21:51,533 --> 00:21:53,800
Come on, let's go.

385
00:21:54,500 --> 00:21:55,400
- Are you ready?
- Let's go.

386
00:21:56,067 --> 00:21:58,200
Mom, I left my phone,
wait a sec.

387
00:21:58,333 --> 00:21:59,233
- Your phone?
- Yes.

388
00:21:59,367 --> 00:22:00,467
- Oh, okay.
- Hi, Auntie Paz!

389
00:22:00,600 --> 00:22:03,633
- Hi, beautiful! Hi, Sis!
- Sis!

390
00:22:03,767 --> 00:22:04,733
What are you doing here?

391
00:22:04,867 --> 00:22:08,967
I brought the papers
you need to sign.

392
00:22:09,900 --> 00:22:12,367
Sis, maybe don't go
into work just yet?

393
00:22:12,500 --> 00:22:14,167
Take a leave for now.

394
00:22:14,733 --> 00:22:16,600
Put your family first.

395
00:22:16,767 --> 00:22:18,767
We'll handle FMP for the moment.

396
00:22:21,500 --> 00:22:23,633
That's exactly
what I was planning, too, Paz.

397
00:22:25,000 --> 00:22:26,867
Things here are getting intense.

398
00:22:27,400 --> 00:22:30,267
Coleen's situation
is really hard.

399
00:22:30,900 --> 00:22:33,967
And Manuel, he's quiet,

400
00:22:35,300 --> 00:22:38,867
but you can see he's devastated
by Jessica's death.

401
00:22:39,367 --> 00:22:41,433
And now, Coleen's
going through something.

402
00:22:42,767 --> 00:22:45,667
Unbelievable, Sis?
You're problems never end,

403
00:22:45,800 --> 00:22:48,633
just keep piling up,
one after another.

404
00:22:49,433 --> 00:22:50,900
Go on, Sis, don't go
into work yet.

405
00:22:51,033 --> 00:22:52,633
Take a short break.

406
00:22:53,000 --> 00:22:55,133
We'll handle the business
for now.

407
00:22:56,267 --> 00:22:57,967
Oh, by the way...

408
00:22:58,100 --> 00:23:00,667
what's happening with
Manuel's annulment?

409
00:23:00,800 --> 00:23:01,767
What's he planning?

410
00:23:01,900 --> 00:23:03,867
And didn't he say he's going
to file a case

411
00:23:04,000 --> 00:23:06,133
against Hazel
for illegal detention?

412
00:23:06,267 --> 00:23:07,367
What's the status on that?

413
00:23:07,833 --> 00:23:08,967
I don't know.

414
00:23:09,100 --> 00:23:13,367
I don't think Manuel can face
all of that yet.

415
00:23:14,367 --> 00:23:17,100
Oh, this should bring a smile
to your face.

416
00:23:17,233 --> 00:23:20,000
Someone left a gift for you
at the guard house.

417
00:23:20,133 --> 00:23:21,267
- Rolly said so, yes.
- A gift?

418
00:23:21,400 --> 00:23:22,900
- From who?
- Well, it's not...

419
00:23:23,067 --> 00:23:25,433
No name, but it's addressed
to you.

420
00:23:25,567 --> 00:23:26,233
Oh.

421
00:23:27,933 --> 00:23:29,100
Go ahead, open it.

422
00:23:30,367 --> 00:23:31,700
Please help me with this.

423
00:23:32,633 --> 00:23:33,967
There.

424
00:23:34,100 --> 00:23:36,100
You really opened it for me.

425
00:23:57,167 --> 00:23:58,900
So what you're saying,
Attorney...

426
00:23:59,467 --> 00:24:01,300
is that no witness came forward

427
00:24:01,433 --> 00:24:03,600
to prove that Coleen
pushed Jessica?

428
00:24:04,567 --> 00:24:05,533
What about the people
commenting online?

429
00:24:05,667 --> 00:24:06,467
What are they?

430
00:24:06,600 --> 00:24:08,267
Scammers?

431
00:24:08,400 --> 00:24:11,733
So reaching out to Detective XY
meant nothing?

432
00:24:11,867 --> 00:24:15,233
Friend, maybe Coleen really
is telling the truth.

433
00:24:15,367 --> 00:24:16,233
Shut up!

434
00:24:17,133 --> 00:24:18,167
How about you, Attorney?

435
00:24:19,367 --> 00:24:22,033
You didn't find any evidence
or eyewitnesses either.

436
00:24:24,000 --> 00:24:25,500
Mrs. Cruz, there really
isn't any.

437
00:24:27,300 --> 00:24:28,933
Not at all, or are you just not
doing anything?

438
00:24:36,033 --> 00:24:37,433
Oh, there you go.

439
00:24:38,867 --> 00:24:40,767
Look at this, Mrs. Cruz.

440
00:24:40,900 --> 00:24:44,800
These are the people we found
who were at the hospital

441
00:24:44,933 --> 00:24:46,767
when Jessica was hit.

442
00:24:48,433 --> 00:24:51,500
None of them saw any pushing.

443
00:24:58,400 --> 00:24:59,467
Hazel did this!

444
00:24:59,600 --> 00:25:00,600
That evil person!

445
00:25:00,733 --> 00:25:01,833
The queen of evil!

446
00:25:02,000 --> 00:25:03,233
No one else
could have done this!

447
00:25:03,367 --> 00:25:04,433
Who else could it be?

448
00:25:12,467 --> 00:25:14,367
How am I supposed to put Coleen
in jail?

449
00:25:24,933 --> 00:25:25,733
What?

450
00:25:26,667 --> 00:25:28,233
You really are a demon!

451
00:25:28,467 --> 00:25:29,767
What did you send me here?

452
00:25:34,067 --> 00:25:36,367
About the annulment
with Hazel...

453
00:25:36,533 --> 00:25:38,833
My mind's been all over
the place.

454
00:25:38,967 --> 00:25:41,233
Maybe I need a breather.

455
00:25:41,367 --> 00:25:42,867
I need to recover first.

456
00:25:43,000 --> 00:25:44,700
I understand.

457
00:25:44,833 --> 00:25:45,933
I can wait.

458
00:25:46,067 --> 00:25:48,233
Mrs. Cruz! It's already
in police custody.

459
00:25:48,367 --> 00:25:50,367
the driver who hit Jessica.

460
00:25:50,500 --> 00:25:52,167
Where is the one
who killed my child?

461
00:25:52,300 --> 00:25:53,667
Where?

462
00:25:53,800 --> 00:25:55,267
- Where?
- Mrs. Cruz, calm down!

463
00:25:55,400 --> 00:25:56,367
Calm down first!

464
00:25:59,333 --> 00:26:01,400
- You animal!
- Ma'am, stop it!

465
00:26:01,533 --> 00:26:02,800
Ma'am! Ma'am, I'm sorry!

466
00:26:02,933 --> 00:26:04,267
Ma'am! Ma'am, sorry!

467
00:26:04,400 --> 00:26:07,700
I'm sorry! I'm sorry!
I'm sorry! I didn't mean it!

468
00:26:07,833 --> 00:26:09,600
I cannot accept your apology!
